"Dont open your eyes, you wont like what you see. The devil's of Truth steal the souls of the free."--Trent Reznor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uswanda08.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swanda08</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 9:01:13 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://broodwar.gcpro.de/fun/fanart/Kyron2_tn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickpocket Policy </span><hr size=1> No matter how &quot;roguelike&quot; it is to pick pocket.. you dont PP something you are stabbing your dagger into as well, it shouldnt be possible to PP something you are attacking, or even better to PP something that is fighting. And saying its ok because casters always want the high prices for items is just BS <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
and since frogs in sebilis drop gems as well it doesnt matter if some mobs are unpickable.. if you have a masterlooter splitting the cash equally and you STILL PP some extra for you I consider this very rude <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zahrdahl>Zahrdahl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 9:23:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickpocket Policy </span><hr size=1> It's one of the tricks of our trade... Verant implemented it for us. Why wouldn't we use it?! People know we have the ability to do it, and still they group with us <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
