 <p><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=135483">Zahrdahl</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uswanda08.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swanda08</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 9:33:49 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://broodwar.gcpro.de/fun/fanart/Kyron2_tn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickpocket Policy </span><hr size=1> good, I am a warrior, therefor as closest to the mob that dies. I could loot it all too, if you ask the right newbies, they would agree with it a &quot;class defining ability&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nenjindarkeyes>Nenjin Darkeyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 9:46:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickpocket Policy </span><hr size=1> And when you do is when the rogues start pickpocketing. Cyclical, dont ya think. <p>Nenjin Darkeyes<BR>
